#Approach:

Approach:
Ye code prefix ko infix me convert karne ke liye reverse traversal + stack of strings use karta hai.

1. Prefix expression ko reverse kar dete hain,
   kyuki prefix me operator pehle hota hai aur hume operands pehle process karne hain.
2. Ab reversed string ko left se right traverse karte hain.
3. Agar operand mile, to usse string bana ke stack me push kar do.
4. Agar operator mile, to stack se top ke 2 expressions pop karo:
   - first pop = left operand/expression
   - second pop = right operand/expression
5. Fir new infix expression banao:
   '(' + first + operator + second + ')'
6. Is new expression ko stack me wapas push kar do.
7. End me stack ka top hi final infix answer hoga.

Main idea:
Prefix me operator apne operands se pehle hota hai,
isliye reverse karke usse postfix jaisa treat karte hain aur stack se combine karte chalte hain.

Time Complexity: O(n)
Space Complexity: O(n)

#Code:

class Solution {

    public boolean isOperator(Character a){
        if((a == '+') || (a == '-') || (a == '*') || (a == '/')){
            return true;
        }
        return false;
    }

    public String prefixToInfix(String s) {
        // Your code goes here
        StringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder(s);
        sb.reverse();
        int n = sb.length();
        int i = 0;
        ArrayDeque<String> stack = new ArrayDeque<>();

        while(i < n){
            char ch = sb.charAt(i);

            //if ch is an operator
            if(isOperator(ch)){
                String first = stack.pop();
                String second = stack.pop();
                String temp = '(' + first + ch + second + ')';
                stack.push(temp);
            }
            //if ch is an operand
            else{
                stack.push(Character.toString(ch));
            }
            i++;
        }
        return stack.peek();
    }
}
